@1  = ~Aurora's Shoes and Boots~
@2  = ~Aurora~

@3  = ~Green Cloak~
@4  = ~This forest-green cloak does not appear to have any special qualities. When you examine it more closely, however, you see that someone has embroidered an ornate golden sun with the letter "A" in front.

STATISTICS:

Weight: 3~

@5  = ~Ornate Ring~
@6  = ~This gold ring is set with an unusually large emerald. Inscribed inside the band are the words "To the sunshine of my life."

STATISTICS:

Equipped Ability: Charisma +1
Weight: 0~

@7  = ~Single Earring~
@8  = ~This large, gold earring is shaped like the sun and set with a gleaming emerald. Its mate, if it ever had one, is missing.

STATISTICS:

Equipped Ability: Protects against critical hits
Weight: 0~

@9  = ~Green Moccasins~
@10 = ~These pale-green, much-worn moccasins still manage to impress you with their elegance. A golden sun is embroidered on each. Primarily of sentimental value to their original owner, they've been thrown at a dragon, washed downstream and worn by who-knows-what over the years.

STATISTICS:

Weight: 2~

@11 = ~Earring~

@12 = ~Jeweled Long Sword +3~
@13 = ~The double-edged blade runs 36 inches in length and tapers to a sharp point. It is a well-forged, efficient-looking weapon without much ornamentation apart from the large green emerald on the pommel.

STATISTICS:

THAC0: +3 bonus
Damage: 1D8 + 3
Damage Type: Slashing
Weight: 2
Speed Factor: 2
Proficiency Type: Long Sword
Type: 1-handed
Requires: 6 Strength
Not Usable By:
 Cleric
 Druid
 Mage~

@14 = ~Aurora gained this sword defending a small, coastal village from pirates. She refused to name it, saying that a named sword doomed its holder to an early death and obscurity. It is enchanted and (more to the point) has a large, green emerald in the pommel.

STATISTICS:

THAC0: +3 bonus
Damage: 1D8 + 3
Damage Type: Slashing
Weight: 2
Speed Factor: 2
Proficiency Type: Long Sword
Type: 1-handed
Requires: 6 Strength
Not Usable By:
 Cleric
 Druid
 Mage~

@15 = ~Ornate Necklace~
@16 = ~This is an attractive golden necklace with a sun-shaped pendant. A dazzling emerald is set in the middle of the pendant, and the letter "A" is etched on the back of it.

STATISTICS:

Weight: 1~

@17 = ~Boots of Endurance~
@18 = ~No one ever warns beginning adventurers just how much walking they'll be doing. The proper footgear can make all the difference, however, and these boots are designed to ensure that you face the last battle of the day feeling as fit as you did the first.

STATISTICS:

Equipped Ability: Constitution +1
Weight: 4~

@19 = ~Boots of High Style~
@20 = ~These boots were created at the request of a bard who wished for higher payment after each performance. They have traveled through many lands and many hands and everyone who has ever worn them agrees on two things: They are dead sexy and excruciatingly painful.

STATISTICS:

Equipped Abilities: Charisma +2, Dexterity -2
Weight: 3~

@21 = ~Boots of Trudging~
@22 = ~These boots were crafted long ago by a monk distressed by the inability of his companions to keep up with his traveling speed. Unable to assist them to travel faster, he took upon himself the discipline of keeping to their pace and ultimately created these boots so that others might follow in his path.

STATISTICS:

Equipped Ability: Movement rate -2
Weight: 4~

@23 = ~Boots of Bravery~
@24 = ~Even the most hardened adventurers are afraid sometimes. Unless they wear these boots, that is. Aurora won't say where she got them, but these boots provide the wearer with protection from all forms of fear.

STATISTICS:

Equipped Ability: Protection from Fear
Weight: 4~

@25 = ~Boots of Battle~
@26 = ~There's nothing like having surprise on your side in a battle, and these boots give the wearer just that. They have been enchanted to enhance a fighter's abilities.

STATISTICS:

Equipped Ability: THAC0 +2
Weight: 4~

@27 = ~Boots of Boredom~
@28 = ~As every adventurer knows, there are days when a bit of boredom would be welcome. Aurora had these made to make sure that those days will happen. Once the wearer slips these shoes on, the day is guaranteed to be boring. No one will attack the wearer. Of course, the wearer can't attack anyone else, either, but if that were possible, the day wouldn't be boring, would it?

STATISTICS:

Equipped Ability: No one attacks the wearer; wearer can walk, talk and hide but is unable to perform any other action
Weight: 4~

@29 = ~These Boots Are Made for Walking~
@30 = ~Walking long distances can be wearing. It gets even harder when one member of the party is weaker than the others. Aurora designed these shoes to make the wearer capable of traveling that extra mile or so before resting.

STATISTICS:

Equipped Ability: Fatigue set to 0
Weight: 3~

@31 = ~Love Lies Bleeding~
@32 = ~In these shoes, it really is possible to knock 'em dead.

STATISTICS:

Special: Cast Nature's Beauty once per day
Weight: 2~

@33 = ~Dancing Shoes~
@34 = ~Dance through the night! In these comfortable, attractive shoes, you'll never have to worry about blisters or stepping on your partner's feet. So what are you waiting for? Go out and party!

STATISTICS:

Equipped Ability: Dexterity +2
Weight: 2~

@35 = ~Long-Leggedy Beasties~
@36 = ~These boots enable the wearer to travel from one adversary to the next with the speed of thought. All the wearer need do is decide whom to attack next. Traveling so quickly does lessen the force of the following blow.

STATISTICS:

Equipped Ability: Movement rate set to 25, but blows cause only 75% damage
Weight: 4~

@37 = ~Shoes of the Shameless~
@38 = ~It's no secret that an adventurer must, on occasion, associate with thieves, murderers, liars, and other forms of scum. A reputation for uprightness and integrity can be a distinct disadvantage on these occasions. The occasional pointless murder can remedy the situation, but it is far easier and less trouble to the conscience to wear these boots instead.

STATISTICS:

Equipped Ability: Reputation -2
Weight: 2~

@39 = ~Boots of the Blameless~
@40 = ~It is no secret that from time to time the adventurer must deal with holier-than-thou paladins, morally upright priests, righteous nobles and other stuffed shirts. A reputation for ruthless efficiency, though commendable in other circumstances, can be a distinct disadvantage during those encounters. A large donation to the local temple can go a long way toward improving relations, but it is far easier and less expensive to wear these boots instead.

STATISTICS:

Equipped Ability: Reputation +2
Weight: 3~

@41 = ~A Mile in Someone Else's Shoes~
@42 = ~Sometimes all an adventurer needs to succeed is a good idea of how the other side thinks. This can be gained through years of study and experience. It can also be gained by wearing these shoes.

STATISTICS:

Equipped Ability: Reverses alignment of wearer
Weight: 2~

@43 = ~Stinky Feet~
@44 = ~His feet stank. They really stank. After several years of snide remarks and requests that he sit somewhere else, anywhere else, he decided to take advantage of the situation. He is still remembered as Stinky Feet, but they say it with respect now.

STATISTICS:

Special: Cast Stinking Cloud once per day
Weight: 4~

@45 = ~Visiting Boots~
@46 = ~After listening to her mother complain about the smell every time Aurora and her companions visited, Aurora commissioned several pair of these. Unlike regular boots, they do not smell bad after a day of walking. In fact, they make it possible to go straight from the street to the house without having to stop for a long wash first.

STATISTICS:

Special: Cast Zone of Sweet Air once per day
Weight: 4~

@47 = ~Boots to Jog the Memory~
@48 = ~A mage Aurora often traveled with was constantly complaining that he didn't have enough fingers to wear helpful rings he needed, and that his amulets were always tangled. So, Aurora commissioned these boots for him.

STATISTICS:

Equipped Ability: Memorize 2 extra level 1 spells and 1 extra level 2 spell
Weight: 4
Usable By:
 Mage
 Bard~

@49 = ~Boots of the Leopard~
@50 = ~The wearer of these boots can spend the day assured that no matter what else goes wrong, at least she's got great shoes.

STATISTICS:

Weight: 3~

@51 = ~Stylish Boots of the Cheetah~
@52 = ~The original Paws of the Cheetah were the property of deadly assassins fond of chasing down their prey. They moved with such speed that their targets often didn't have the opportunity to respond, even on horseback. This was very impressive, of course, but the assassins had no sense of style, so Aurora had a similar pair made in a more attractive cheetah-skin pattern. They increase the wearer's speed and look good at the same time.

STATISTICS:

Equipped Ability: Movement rate doubled
Weight: 3~

@53 = ~Mad Marv's Moccasins~
@54 = ~Mad Marv's favorite saying was "You're only paranoid if they are not after you." He was so convinced that legions of enemies hunted him that he made these moccasins to help him fight his battles. They help their wearer spot the enemy before the enemy spots them. Unfortunately, they also give their wearer a share of Marv's well-known edginess.

STATISTICS:

Special: Attack Speed set to zero; 40% chance of panic for 6 rounds
Weight: 2~

@55 = ~Everyday Green Boots~
@56 = ~These are comfortable, sturdy boots designed for everyday wear. Aurora dyed these her favorite color green, and designed them specially to withstand piercing attacks.

STATISTICS:

Equipped Ability: AC -2 vs. piercing weapons
Weight: 4~

@57 = ~Hand Lotion~
@58 = ~Aurora swears by this lotion which she used when she was adventuring. It keeps the hands soft and supple, avoiding the clumsiness caused by excessive chapping.

STATISTICS:

Special: Dexterity +1 for 6 turns
Weight: 1~

@59 = ~Pink Boots of Stealth~
@60 = ~These boots are perfect for those who wish to be able to move silently. Aurora had them custom-dyed at Imoen's request.

STATISTICS:

Equipped Abilities:
 Move Silently: +20%
 Hide in Shadows: +15%
Weight: 4
Usable By:
 Thief
 Ranger
 Monk~

@61 = ~Muscle Balm~
@62 = ~This is a balm for soothing sore or strained muscles.

STATISTICS:

Special: Fatigue set to 0
Weight: 1~

@63 = ~Pieces of jewelry worn in the ears are common in many cultures. Some rare earrings have had enchantments placed upon them that confer various magical abilities. These earrings are highly sought after, especially by those of the adventuring profession.~

@64 = ~Shoes~
@65 = ~Cobblers normally hand-craft shoes or moccasins such as these. Common shoes are made by using a pattern, but good shoes are designed for the foot of an individual.

STATISTICS:

Weight: 2~

@66 = ~Boots of the Bar~
@67 = ~Sometimes, the weary adventurer needs a good, stiff drink and a nice, soft bed in which to sleep it off afterwards. All the wearer needs to do is click the heels of these boots together three times and the entire party will be transported to an inn of choice.

STATISTICS:

Special: Teleport party to an inn of choice (3 per day)
Weight: 4~

@68 = ~Green-Laced Boots~
@69 = ~Aurora had these boots commissioned shortly after losing her first pair of "adventuring boots" - as soon as she could afford to, that is. Lacing on such an attractive pair of boots gave a good start to any day, and they provide an additional aid by boosting the wearer's defenses. Due to many compliments from her customers, Aurora produced more of the boots and made them available more widely.

STATISTICS:

Equipped Abilities: AC -1, Saving throws -1
Weight: 4~

@70 = ~Robe~
@71 = ~This is a common, lightweight robe woven of linen, with sleeves of finer silk. It appears to be an all-purpose garment well-suited for any profession.

STATISTICS:

Weight: 3~

@72 = ~Green Robe~
@73 = ~In return for services rendered as guides and guards, and as a gesture of friendship, a wizard enchanted these robes for the three members of his elite bodyguard. The robes provide protection against various forms of magic, and make the wearer more agile. In addition, they bring out the color of the wearer's eyes.

STATISTICS:

Equipped Abilities:
 AC: base set to 4
 Magic Resistance +15%
 Dexterity +1
Weight: 3~

@74 = ~Everyday Yellow Boots~
@75 = ~These are comfortable, sturdy boots designed for everyday wear. Aurora dyed these yellow, and designed them specially to withstand blunt attacks.

STATISTICS:

Equipped Ability: AC -2 vs. blunt weapons
Weight: 4~

@76 = ~Everyday Blue Boots~
@77 = ~These are comfortable, sturdy boots designed for everyday wear. Aurora dyed these dark blue, and designed them specially to withstand slashing attacks.

STATISTICS:

Equipped Ability: AC -2 vs. slashing weapons
Weight: 4~

@78 = ~Pearwood Shoe Box~
@79 = ~This light, sturdy box is made of a fine-grained hardwood and is bound with iron. It is compact and looks very serviceable.~
@80 = ~Aurora designed this box to hold her many shoes and boots. It is compact, sturdy and made of a varnished pearwood bound with iron. She had a wizard friend enchant it so that it opens onto another self-contained mini-plane. A large quantity of boots may be placed in the box, yet its weight stays the same.

STATISTICS:

Capacity: 40 boots or shoes
Weight: 2~

@81 = ~Acid Rapier +2~
@82 = ~This ornate basket-hilted rapier is made of an unusual bronze and adamant alloy harder than steel. The age-darkened hilt is acid-etched with gold and silver scrollwork and embossed with an unknown coat-of-arms. Although the blade can corrode whatever it touches, the weapon itself withstands any corrosion. No one knows where the unusual blade came from originally, but it figures in many tales and legends. Pirates, treasure hunters and unsavory rogues alike have long coveted the rapier.

STATISTICS:

THAC0: +2
Damage: 1D6 + 1
 +2 Acid Damage
Damage Type: Piercing
Weight: 3
Speed Factor: 2
Proficiency Type: Short Sword
Type: 1-handed
Requires: 5 Strength
Not Usable By:
 Cleric
 Druid
 Mage~

@83 = ~Pirate's Cutlass +2~
@84 = ~This fearsome blade of curved steel once belonged to the notorious Black Dhavrag, scourge of the Sword Coast. With this sword constantly in his hand, the pirate king plundered many a coastal village from Amn all the way to Waterdeep, often in a berserk rage. Sadly for him (and gladly for nearly everyone else), he lost it in a card wager and it was carried off during the drunken brawl that followed. So infamous is the cutlass that the mere touch of it can cause a victim to flee in abject terror.

STATISTICS:

THAC0: +2
Damage: 1D6 + 2
Damage Type: Slashing
Equipped Ability: Dexterity +1
Special:
 10% chance to inflict Horror on victim
 10% chance to inflict Berserk on wielder
Weight: 3
Speed Factor: 3
Proficiency Type: Scimitar/Wakizashi/Ninja-To
Type: 1-handed
Requires: 8 Strength
Not Usable By:
 Cleric
 Mage~

@85 = ~Hazel Ioun Stone~
@86 = ~The swashbuckler Aloysius D'Abetot once traveled the Realms from icecaps to deserts, seeking to plunder everything in sight. He relied on this otherworldly luckstone to keep his skull intact during his pillaging. After a particularly long day of thieving, he fell asleep in a tavern garden with a bar wench, the stone safe in his pouch (so he thought). Alas, during his nap, the stone must have wandered off, for he awoke to find it missing, along with the bar wench. Although Aloysius and his antics have long been forgotten, the stone has moved on to impart its luck on a new master. Oddly, it looks much like an acorn.

STATISTICS:

Equipped Abilities: Luck +1; Protects against critical hits
Weight: 1~

@87 = ~Boots of Speed: "The Paws of the Cheetah"
These enchanted boots were once the property of an order of deadly assassins fond of chasing down their prey. They moved with such speed that their targets often didn't have the opportunity to respond, even on horseback. Over time the order's infamy spread, and though its name was never known, all knew to fear the words last heard by their victims: "you can hide, but you cannot run!"

STATISTICS

Equipped Ability: Movement rate doubled
Weight: 4~

@88 = ~Boots of Avoidance: "Senses of the Cat"
The magic of these boots was specifically designed to detect incoming missiles and aid the wearer in avoiding them. They were originally commissioned by the instructors of an archery academy, who had tired of suffering "accidents" at the hands of their inexperienced students.

STATISTICS:

Equipped Ability: AC -5 vs. missile weapons
Weight: 4~

@89 = ~Boots of Grounding: "Talos' Gift"
Untold years ago, the Fortress of the Starspire Peninsula was placed under the direct torment of Talos when a favored Stormherald was murdered there. Talos promised the destruction of the city by earthquakes, its inundation by tidal waves, and the death of its citizens by storms. One pair of these boots was bestowed to ensure that none but a single man would survive to tell the story of his wrath. Later, travelers seeking fortune in the ruined city came upon an aged man, maddened by the continuous destruction around him. The boots he wore would carry to many a distant land the legend of a city consumed by a god's rage. Over the years, others have found the boots useful, and have had skilled mages craft additional pairs.

STATISTICS:

Equipped Ability: Electricity Resistance +50%
Weight: 4~

@90 = ~Boots of Berserking~
@91 = ~Boots of Berserking: "Fury of Ruathym"
Valthjof of Ruathym was an adept shaman of the northmen. So skilled was he that he could summon up wild beasts and infuse their spirits into inanimate objects. Thus did he enchant several pairs of boots for the crew of the longship "Ice Serpent." They rampaged the Moonshaes to the south and did not stop there. Due to the berserk fury the boots gave them, their lust for blood never ceased until each of them lay dead in far corners of the Realms.

STATISTICS

Special: Attacks per round +1 for 20 seconds
Penalties: AC +8; saving throws +6; thief skills and spells disabled
Weight: 3~

@92 = ~Boots of Lightning Speed: "Heels of the Coward"
These modified boots of speed were originally intended to boost the wearer's speed rating even more so than would normal boots of speed. When used, the wearer's movement rate increases as if under the effect of normal boots of speed combined with a haste spell. Unfortunately, the wearer cannot attack or cast spells. Their nickname summarizes their most obvious use: running away.

STATISTICS

Equipped Ability: Movement rate set to maximum
Penalties: Unable to attack or cast spells
Weight: 3~

@93 = ~Legend holds that the mage who created these magical boots trapped the spirits of actual gargoyles within them. However, when the nameless wizard was constructing his third pair of boots, one of the gargoyle's mates appeared and took her vengeance on him.

STATISTICS:

Equipped Ability: Immunity to backstab
Special: Stoneskin 2 times/day (2 skins per use)
Weight: 1~

@94 = ~Installing Aurora's Shoes for Tutu.~
@95 = ~Installing Aurora's Shoes for Baldur's Gate Trilogy.~
@96 = ~Installing Aurora's Shoes for Baldur's Gate II.~
@97 = ~This mod is not compatible with your game. Please check your install folder and try again.~

@98 = ~Boots of War~
@99 = ~These boots of hardened plate metal are enameled with topaz. They have been refashioned from the Boots of Bravery and the Boots of Battle. Thus, they provide the wearer with protection from all forms of fear. In addition, they bear an enchantment that gives the wearer an extra edge over one's opponents in battle.

STATISTICS:

Equipped Abilities:
 Protection from Fear
 THAC0 +2
Weight: 4~

